title: Fort kickers stay healthy for playoffs
text:
With an eye on the playoff’s, the Fort Atkinson boys’ soccer team focused more on health and rest than on the game against Hartford on Thursday at Jones Dairy Farm Stadium. 
The Blackhawks lost 11-1, but came out unscathed for its WIAA regional match on Tuesday. 
“It wasn’t all negative believe it or not, we actually got our seeding, we’re the fifth seed in our region and we play Waterford in Waterford, they’re 6-11 on the year and we have a real shot in the game,” said head coach Kent Lovejoy. “We played our starters for the first 35 minutes or so and we started subbing very, very heavily.” 
With starters in, the Blackhawks gave up a goal in the first couple minute, and had a chance to respond through Kevin England before the team changes, but England put a close range shot just over the net to keep it 1-0 before Hartford started the scoring up again in the 35th minute. 
The Blackhawks’ game at Waterford starts at 7 p.m. on Tuesday.
